## The Public Editor's thoughts

Another metric of how prominent and controversial Maslin Nir's investigation: Times Public Editor Margaret Sullivan wrote two columns about it:

- In July 2015, Sullivan reviewed the NYT's response to Bernstein and agreed with its strong defense of Maslin Nir's "impressive and admirable" work: [Criticism of 'Unvarnished' Brings a Strong Times Defense](http://publiceditor.blogs.nytimes.com/2015/07/29/criticism-of-unvarnished-brings-a-strong-times-defense/)
- A few months later in November, Sullivan sat down with Maslin Nir's editors to hear their response to Reason's Epstein's criticism. Sullivan found their explanations regarding employment ads to be "particularly troubling". She also found "convincing" Epstein's argument that the NYT's claims aren't fully supported by the available studies [New Questions on Nail Salon Investigation, and a Times Response](http://publiceditor.blogs.nytimes.com/2015/11/06/new-questions-on-nail-salon-investigation-and-a-times-response/).

Sullivan concluded that the Times "write further follow-up stories, including some that re-examine its original findings and that take on the criticism from salon owners and others — not defensively but with an open mind."





# Beyond New York

New York may be the nail salon capital, but it's unlikely to be the only place where they've been an issue with regards to labor and workplace safety laws.

Back in 2012, the Los Angeles Times [reported on a state investigation that found toxic chemicals in nail products claiming to be toxic-free](http://articles.latimes.com/2012/apr/10/local/la-me-health-nail-salons-20120410). After the NYT's investigation, the [LAT wrote that its readers wanted to know more](http://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-ln-how-safe-are-california-nail-salons-20150508-story.html). In August of 2015, the LAT covered a forum in Little Saigon [as nail salon workers spoke up on abuse and wage theft](http://www.latimes.com/local/california/la-me-nail-salon-rights-20150807-story.html). In April 2016, Gov. Brown signed [a bill](http://www.leginfo.ca.gov/pub/15-16/bill/asm/ab_2001-2050/ab_2025_cfa_20160411_100939_asm_comm.html) to increase education on labor laws, particularly in nail salons.

The NYT's investigation reached the national level as U.S. Senators Blumenthal and Schumer called on [OSHA to update safety standards at nail salons](https://www.shrm.org/resourcesandtools/hr-topics/risk-management/pages/osha-safety-nail-salons.aspx). In 2006, the [Seattle Post-Intelligencer](http://www.seattlepi.com/lifestyle/health/article/Nail-salons-workers-clients-at-risk-from-toxic-1221426.php) covered an EPA-led initiative to study air quality in salons.
